13/04/2006
STRASBOURG, France -- Romanian Foreign Minister Mihai Razvan Ungureanu presented a report to the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe (PACE) on Wednesday (12 April), detailing the activities of Romania's chairmanship of the CoE Committee of Ministers. 
He highlighted the efforts to enhance democracy, good governance and respect for human rights, in order to promote democratic stability in Europe and boost intercultural dialogue. 
The country's six-month mandate expires at the end of May. 
(Nine o'clock - 13/04/06; CoE Web site - 12/04/06)
